text: I'll just say what you might not want to hear, I'm a huge Pac fan! And I'm white!!!!! This movie is a total disgrace to Tupac's legacy! Granted, I haven't watched it yet, but this trailer is all about Pac being a gangster rapper. Which he wasn't! There's nothing mentioned about his past! Growing up in Baltimore, being a son of a Black Panther, actually being born in prison! Nothing about 	Lesane Parish Crooks, Pac's real name. He went to a performance arts high school and studied ballet at one point. This movie isn't a story about the man that you didn't see, it's a gimmick to make money from his name and his death. Both Pac and Afeni Shakur will be rolling over in their graves when this comes out! If you want the real story, check out Tupac: Resserection the documentary and pick up "Holler If You Hear Me" by Eric Michael Dyson. When Pac was alive, they wanted us to think that he was just a gangster rapper. That's how they made money from him! But he was more, way way more than that!!!!!! Don't belive what you see from this, and if you really want to know the real Pac? Do yourself a favor and research the real man!

text: I just went to go see this movie yesterday. Let me just say as a true fan it was alright but it really didn't do anything for me. They went over shit that everyone knows already we don't need a fucking movie for that lol. I hate to say this but you guys as hard as we try to find out what we think happened that will never happen for us okay. The only person that knows everything about 2pac, his life, his journey, his death IS 2PAC! CASE CLOSED! (And also his loved ones and the people that were very very close to him.) They can come out with 10,000 movies if they want to but it will never work because it's all Hollywood BULLSHIT!! Everyone that was around him the night he got into that fight that ended up in the result of him being shot knows what happened  but some ended up dead and others just didn't want to say anything and you know what they don't have to. It's been 21 years it's time to let him rest in peace and let's just be grateful for the legacy that he has left us and cherish what we still have of him. (Videos, Movies, Interviews) It's time to shut the movies and the stories down. We need to start having more biopics of the legends that are still here to tell us their story and let our deceased legends REST IN PEACE!

text: One topic people glance over but yet it is a constant reminder in most Hip Hop movies or movies that are similar in content and that is the history of the Black Panthers. They were a powerful organization and a much needed movement at that time but the government systematically got rid of them through incarceration and murder! I was around back then and remember all the good things the Panthers tried to do for their communities and the Black race.  But the USA government supposed that they were a threat too powerful for their own good. They were a very intelligent group of people well organized and well read! they knew the law and could look law enforcement straight in the eye and ask intelligent questions and gave intelligent answers.They didn't shuffle and jive and scratch were they didn't itch... Some of you younger people need to take some time out to read up on the history of the Black Panthers, so when you see movies like All Eyez on me, you will understand why Tupac's mother was framed and whyTupac stopped his concert to acknowledge H. Newton in the audience. ‚úä
